ggplot is soooooo cool.. lol..

Plot

library(ggplot2)
ggplot(data = gapminder, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp, color = continent)) + 
  geom_point(shape = 17,size = 0.5) +
  scale_x_log10() +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", size = 0.5)

Hiding the code/editing stuff

#({r Plot hidden, echo = FALSE, results = 'hide', eval = FALSE, warning=FALSE}) library(ggplot2) ggplot(data = gapminder, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp, color = continent)) + geom_point(shape = 17,size = 0.5) + scale_x_log10() + geom_smooth(method = "lm", size = 0.5)

editing the Plot
